import numpy
import pandas as pd
import pandas_datareader as pd_reader
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import datetime
from pandas.plotting import register_matplotlib_converters
import requests_cache

############################## PRELUDE ##############################

# initiate converters
register_matplotlib_converters()

# rc config
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [20, 8]
plt.rcParams['figure.titlesize'] = 'large'
plt.rcParams['figure.titleweight'] = 'bold'
plt.rcParams['xtick.labelsize'] = plt.rcParams['ytick.labelsize'] = 15
plt.rcParams['axes.titlesize'] = 'large'
plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 20
plt.rcParams['font.weight'] = 'bold'
plt.rcParams['axes.labelweight'] = "bold"
plt.rcParams['axes.titlepad'] = 10
plt.rcParams['axes.titleweight'] = "bold"
plt.rcParams['legend.fontsize'] = 14
plt.rcParams["lines.linewidth"] = 2.5
plt.style.use('dark_background')

expire_after = datetime.timedelta(days=1)
session = requests_cache.CachedSession(cache_name='cache', backend='sqlite', expire_after=expire_after)

start = datetime.datetime(1990, 6, 1)
end = datetime.date.today()

def fred_reader(symbol):
    return pd_reader.data.DataReader(symbol, 'fred', start, end, session=session)

def try_draw_span(ax, begin, end, leftmost):
    if begin > leftmost:
        ax.axvspan(begin, end, color='tab:grey', alpha=0.3)

def plot_recession(ax, leftmost):
    recs = fred_reader('USREC').query('USREC==1')
    recs_90 = recs.loc['1990':'1991']
    recs_2k = recs.loc['2001']
    recs_2k8 = recs.loc['2008':]
    recs90_bgn = recs_90.index[0]
    recs90_end = recs_90.index[-1]
    recs2k_bgn = recs_2k.index[0]
    recs2k_end = recs_2k.index[-1]
    recs2k8_bgn = recs_2k8.index[0]
    recs2k8_end = recs_2k8.index[-1]
    try_draw_span(ax, recs90_bgn, recs90_end, leftmost)
    try_draw_span(ax, recs2k_bgn, recs2k_end, leftmost)
    try_draw_span(ax, recs2k8_bgn, recs2k8_end, leftmost)
    
def add_source(ax, annotation):
    plt.text(0, -0.1, annotation,
      horizontalalignment='left',
      verticalalignment='center',
      fontsize=14,
      transform = ax.transAxes)
    plt.text(0, -0.15, "©: Bateman Capital",
      horizontalalignment='left',
      verticalalignment='center',
      fontsize=14,
      transform = ax.transAxes)

def invert(df):
    col = df.columns[0]
    df[col] = df[col].map (lambda spread: -spread)
    return df

def shift_days(s, days):
    return s.shift(days, freq='D')

def draw_df(df, title):
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

    ax1_label = 'Volatility'
    ax1.set_ylabel(ax1_label)
    ax1.tick_params(axis='y')
    ax1.plot(df.VIXCLS, color='tab:red', label="VIX")
    ax1.plot(df.VXNCLS, color='tab:orange', label="VXN")
    ax1.legend(loc='upper left')
    #ax1.set_xlim(left=datetime.date(1990, 1, 1), right=datetime.date(2022, 1, 1)) # don't let shade block legend
    ax1.set_yscale('linear') # can be log

    ax2_color = 'tab:blue'
    label_2y = '10y-2Y (invert, 24M ahead)'
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    ax2.set_ylabel('inv-spread (percentage)')
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y')
    ax2.plot(df.T10Y2Y, color=ax2_color, label=label_2y)
    ax2.set_ylim(top=4, bottom=-5)

    ax3_color = 'tab:purple'
    label_3m = '10y-3M (invert, 24M ahead)'
    ax2.plot(df.T10Y3M, color=ax3_color, label=label_3m)

    ax4_color = 'tab:cyan'
    label_ff = '10y-FF (invert, 24M ahead)'
    ax2.plot(df.T10YFF, color=ax4_color, label=label_ff)

    # spread invert line
    ax2.axhline(y=0, color='orange', linestyle='-', linewidth=4.0, alpha=0.5)

    #plot_recession(ax2, df.dropna().index[0])

    ax2.legend(loc='upper right')

    # stretch
    plt.subplots_adjust(left=0.1, right=1.0)
    plt.title(title)

    add_source(ax1, "Source: Federal Reserve Bank of St.Louis")

    ax1.grid(alpha=0.3)
    plt.show()
    
draw_df(df, "Inverse 10Y Spread advanced 24 Months vs VIX")
draw_df(df.dropna().rolling(50).mean(), "Inverse 10Y Spread advanced 24 Months vs VIX (SMA-50)")
draw_df(df.dropna().rolling(200).mean(), "Inverse 10Y Spread advanced 24 Months vs VIX (SMA-200)")
